HEADWORD: Hygroscopicity
<hw>Hy`gro*sco*pic"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The property possessed by vegetable tissues of
absorbing or discharging moisture according to circumstances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

